## Errors & Mistakes
- BIG GOTCHA: the Bash `grep` alias here is ripgrep. `grep \"a\\|b\"` searches the
  LITERAL string a|b (escaped pipe = literal in RG), and `grep -E`/`--include`
  ERROR OUT. My early \\|-alternation greps silently returned false 'no matches',
  which nearly made me flag the llamaindex vector_index/*.json fixtures as orphans
  — they are actually loaded by DIRECTORY path (StorageContext.from_defaults(
  persist_dir=...)) in test_llamaindex_quick_start. Use the Grep tool or
  /usr/bin/grep. Saved a memory about this.

## gt / branch mechanics
- Workspace branch andrew/find-unused-files == origin/master tip; local `master`
  is 173 commits BEHIND origin/master and is checked out in the main worktree
  (/Users/andrew/conductor/weave), so it can't be fast-forwarded from here.
- gt trunk = local master. `gt create` refused (untracked current branch). So I
  used git checkout -b off HEAD, committed, then `gt track --parent master`.
- gt reports '174 commits' for this branch (173 stale-trunk + 1 real). This is
  COSMETIC: origin/master..HEAD == 1. GitHub PR base=master will show only the
  1 deletion commit. `gt sync`/refreshing local master clears the display.

